column5: Had the pleasure of meeting a whole bunch of people I never met before today, it was a great time, even wandered out on the ice.  Pretty sure it was the biggest turnout so far, with around 140 people registered.. I think.
meh, thats just a baby laker   ....looks fun!
Wish I could have made it

THANKS TO TYLER'S FAMILY FOR PUTTING ON A GREAT EVENT  My Wife and I had a great time.  Its was good meeting you today TJ,   I look forward in meeting again in the future  I AM HAVING PERCH BURGERS THAT WAS COOKED ON MY NEW FISH FRYER and WINGS  for my wife LOL  Thanks again  DAVE
That was a whack of perch you got!!
Doug Mackie wins it!  Nice job buddy
It was a great time with great people. Nice meeting You TJ.
Great pics TJ.  Sorry we missed it this year.  Paul is on call and has been called in twice  Nice laker.  Joey

It was an awesome turn out for sure  ,met a lot a new people out there today.Too many people to list,It was great to finally meet you guys.You too T J even though you forgot the hat  ,Ill just wear the OFC mug on my melon in the mean time

Great time today meeting up with some old friends & meeting some new ones. To bad the fish in the deep water didn't co-operate for me.   Lots of lookers but not big on being takers. Only one bite which I lost after a long battle including the fish running off quite a bit of line. Hook broke off the jig. Still have the jig just no hook. On the way in I stopped in 47 fow for 10 mins. to try for perch. That worked out pretty good. Landed 3 fish in 10 mins. including one which got me 3rd place in the perch category. I sure like my new cast iron pot & lid. After the tourny I went back out with the same results in the deeper water. Move back to the same spot for perch and got bites as quick as I could get my maggot tip jig back down until 5:50 pm when the bite just shut down. As I said great day.  Best Wishes: Rick
You can thank the gent that donated it,Its was written on the top of the box.Not me but a good old friend of mine.Enjoy it, I was thinking of buying one just like it.Im glad you like it.
Well thanks to R.H. from Home Hardware (Hamilton?).
I will let him know for sure.But he should of picked up the phone earlier.NO WHITTEY FOR HIM TONIGHT.

I'm glad to be a part of another successful Tyler fundraiser and fishing day in 2010.  There was a really great turnout yesterday, maybe the biggest ever, and as a result there were a lot of fish brought in which was nice to see.  You could tell by all the smiles and the sound of laughter that everyone had a good time.  Congrats to the big Laker caught by Doug, I think, and also to the guy who caught that massive Whitefish, some real impressive fish guys!!  I didn't see the winning Perch but I think it was around 11 or 12"..not too shabby either.  Hopefully Tyler continues to inspire those around him and improve with the love and support of his family and 'community'  Until next year, good fishing.  Tony
Always a great event.  Nice too see so many fish caught, good weather and get people.  Hope this year that made the most $$ yet, Such a nice family  We did miss you Maureen
It was another great event, the best yet.  Glad to be a part of it again. Everyone looked like they had a good time.  Congrats to the winners.  Aaron
T.J you could of at least got a better pic of MEEEEE you should have used my GOOOOOOD side....
